sense.def:
To enter a place
pomeni priti ali iti v neki prostor.

seg.quote: They stopped talking as soon as they saw Brody enter.

sense.def:
To enter an organization, institution, or profession
pomeni postati član neke organizacije, ustanove ali poklica ali začeti sodelovati v njih.

Če nova lastnost ali poteza
enters something
, se v nečem pokaže.

seg.quote: A note of resolution entered the bishop's voice.

sense.def:
Kadar nekaj
enters a new period in its development or history
, začenja novo obdobje v svoji zgodovini.

seg.quote: The industry entered a period of lower growth.

sense.def:
To enter a competition or race
ali
to enter for a competition or race
pomeni sodelovati na tekmovanju ali v dirki.

To enter something in a book or computer
pomeni vpisati v knjigo ali vtipkati na računalnik.

seg.quote: Enter it in the cash book.

sense.def:
To enter into something important or complicated
pomeni začeti delati ali se vplesti v nekaj pomembnega ali zapletenega.

seg.quote: The Labour Government refused to enter into negotiations.

sense.def:
Kadar nekaj
enters into something
, je dejavnik nečesa.

seg.quote: Obviously personal relationships enter into it.
